To summarise, prior works have shown that relational knowledge is captured by LLMs to a certain extent. However, there is still insufficient understanding of how performance differs across different kinds of knowledge or relations, for instance, commonsense knowledge compared to entity-centric encyclopedic facts or transversal versus hierarchical relations. In addition, several studies raise questions about LLMs capacity to infer knowledge beyond already-seen statements.